x4freetext: POLARIZED NEUTRON CAPTURE ON 13-C.
POLARIZED AND UNPOLARIZED DEUTERONS ON DEUTERIUM
GAS. NEUTRON BEAM POLARIZATION = 0.57 WITH
DEUTERON POLARIZATION = 0.65.
NEUTRON ENERGY RESOLUTION 0.40 MEV AT 7.75 MEV,
0.18 MEV AT 17.0 MEV.
NE213 SCINTILLATOR AT ZERO DEGREES WAS USED TO
MONITOR THE NEUTRON BEAM.
GAMMA DETECTION SYSTEM CONSISTED OF TWO
25CM BY 25CM CYLINDRICAL NAI SCINTILLATORS.
32.4 GRAMS OF 96.4 PERCENT ISOTOPICALLY PURE
13-C IN THE FORM OF FINE POWDER.
SPECTRA WERE ANALYSED WITH XSYS AND MULFIT CODES.
TARGET-OUT BACKGROUNDS WERE NORMALIZED AND SUBTRACTED
FROM TARGET-IN SPECTRA. THE SPECTRA WERE FIT TO
STANDARD LINE SHAPE OF THE NAI DETECTOR RESPONSE
FUNCTION. THE NUMBER OF COUNTS IN THE PEAK REGIONS
WERE NORMALIZED TO BEAM CURRENT INTEGRATION, DEAD
TIMES, ACCIDENTAL COINCIDENCE RATES AND FOR SOME OF
THE DATA TO THE ZERO DEGREE NEUTRON MONITOR.
ONE STANDARD DEVIATION OF THE
STATISTICAL ERROR.
M.C.WRIGHT, 85/4/18.
DATA FROM TABLE A-1 OF THE THESIS.
